# Cloud Chaser

Production-oriented two-stage cloud identification:

1. YOLO segmentation finds cloud/sky foreground in outdoor scenes.
2. A PyTorch classifier assigns one of the seven GCD cloud classes to each detected crop.
3. Inference overlays masks, boxes, and labels such as `1_cumulus - 94%`.

## File Structure

```text
cloud_chaser/
  data/                 ADE20K, GCD, TJNU datasets and augmentations
  models/               YOLO wrapper, classifier backbones, SimCLR
  utils/                checkpoints, metrics, visualization
  training.py           SSL, classifier, and detector training loops
  evaluation.py         detector mask-mAP and ADE validation mIoU
configs/default.yaml    centralized configuration
train.py                training and evaluation CLI
inference.py            end-to-end prediction CLI
export.py               ONNX/TorchScript/export CLI
scripts/                dataset preparation helpers
```

## Installation

Use Python 3.10, 3.11, or 3.12. Python 3.14 is not recommended for this stack yet because PyTorch, OpenCV, Albumentations, and transitive native packages may not provide wheels and can fall back to fragile source builds.

```bash
python3.12 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -e .
```

For CUDA training, install the CUDA-enabled PyTorch wheels first, then install the project. Example for CUDA 12.1:

```bash
python3.12 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
pip install -e .
python -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available()); print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0) if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'no cuda')"
```

If your system only has Python 3.14 as `python3`, install a supported interpreter first. On Ubuntu releases whose apt repositories do not ship `python3.12`, `uv` is the quickest option:

```bash
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh
source "$HOME/.local/bin/env"
uv python install 3.12
uv venv --python 3.12 .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
pip install -e .
```

On Ubuntu releases that do ship Python 3.12 packages:

```bash
sudo apt install python3.12 python3.12-venv python3.12-dev
```

Expected local datasets:

```text
data/ADE20K/images/training/*.jpg
data/ADE20K/images/validation/*.jpg
data/ADE20K/annotations/training/*.png
data/ADE20K/annotations/validation/*.png
data/GCD/train/<class>/*.jpg
data/GCD/test/<class>/*.jpg
data/TJNU/**/*.jpg                 # optional, for SimCLR pretraining
```

This ADE20K checkout exposes `sky` as class `3`; `cloud` is not present in `objectInfo150.txt`. The converter requests both and falls back to class ID `3`, controlled in `configs/default.yaml`.

## Training

Prepare ADE20K as YOLO segmentation data:

```bash
python3 -m scripts.prepare_ade20k_yolo --config configs/default.yaml
```

Train the segmentation model:

```bash
python3 train.py detector --config configs/default.yaml
```

Pretrain the classifier encoder with SimCLR on unlabeled TJNU:

```bash
python3 train.py ssl --config configs/default.yaml
```

Fine-tune the 7-class GCD classifier:

```bash
python3 train.py classifier --config configs/default.yaml
```

To use the SimCLR encoder, set `classifier.ssl_checkpoint: runs/ssl/best.pt` in the config before classifier training.

## Optional Detector Crops for Classifier Data

If you want the classifier fine-tuned on detector-generated crops rather than full GCD frames:

```bash
python3 -m scripts.build_cloud_crops \
  --input-root data/GCD \
  --output-root data/GCD_crops \
  --detector-weights runs/detector/weights/best.pt
```

Then set `data.gcd_root: data/GCD_crops`.

## Evaluation

Segmentation reports Ultralytics mask mAP plus foreground mIoU on ADE20K validation:

```bash
python3 train.py eval-detector --config configs/default.yaml
```

Classification reports Top-1 accuracy and macro F1 on GCD test:

```bash
python3 train.py eval-classifier --config configs/default.yaml
```

## Inference

```bash
python3 inference.py \
  --config configs/default.yaml \
  --image examples/outdoor_scene.jpg \
  --output runs/inference/outdoor_scene.jpg
```

The inference path performs YOLO-Seg, masks/crops each detected instance, batches the crops through the classifier with mixed precision when CUDA is available, and writes an annotated image.

## Export

```bash
python3 export.py detector --config configs/default.yaml --format onnx
python3 export.py classifier --config configs/default.yaml --format onnx --output runs/classifier/best.onnx
python3 export.py classifier --config configs/default.yaml --format torchscript --output runs/classifier/best.torchscript
```

## Notes

- Detector architecture is configured as `yolo11s-seg.pt`; switch to `yolov8s-seg.pt` in `configs/default.yaml` if preferred.
- Classifier backbones supported now: `resnet50`, `efficientnet_b0`, `densenet121`.
- Augmentations include RandomShadow, GaussianBlur, horizontal flips, and conservative vertical flips for cloud texture robustness.
